# agnosticv Repo Workflow

## Repo Location

The agnosticv repo is at `~/Documents/GitHub/agnosticv` (remote: `rhpds/agnosticv`). It is a separate repo from this collection. The default branch is `master`.

## Where Lab Config Lives

The LB2961 lab config file is:
```
sandboxes-gpte/AI_DRIVEN_ANSIBLE_AUTOMATION/common.yaml
```

This file defines instances, security groups, workloads, AAP configuration, EDA setup, and all variables consumed by this Ansible collection's roles at deploy time.

**Note**: There may also be a `summit-2025/lb2961-ai-driven-ansible-automation/common.yaml` on feature branches — but the canonical path on `master` is under `sandboxes-gpte/`.

## PR Workflow

### Contributing to an existing PR

To push a commit to someone else's open PR:

```bash
cd ~/Documents/GitHub/agnosticv
git fetch origin <branch-name>
git checkout <branch-name>
# Make changes, then:
git add <files>
git commit -m "description"
git push origin <branch-name>
```

Use `gh pr view <number> --json headRefName` to find the branch name.

### Creating a new PR

Always branch from `origin/master`:

```bash
git fetch origin master
git checkout -b feat/<descriptive-name> origin/master
# Make changes, commit, then:
git push -u origin feat/<descriptive-name>
gh pr create --base master --title "..." --body "..."
```

## Pre-commit Hook

The agnosticv repo has a `rh-multi-pre-commit` hook for leak detection. It runs automatically on commit. If it blocks a commit, do NOT skip it with `--no-verify` — fix the leak.

## Variable Naming

Variables set in `common.yaml` flow into this collection's roles via their `defaults/main.yml`. Match variable names exactly (e.g., `lightspeed_mcp_client_id` in agnosticv must match `lightspeed_mcp_client_id` in `roles/lightspeed_mcp_server/defaults/main.yml`).
